  "extraHighlightWords": [],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Tuesday. I said I would not have to wait long for William's next disaster, and I was right.",
      "zh": "星期二。我說過不用等太久就會看到 William 的下一場災難，果然被我說中了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "This morning, William decided he was a brave knight defending our living room from an invisible dragon.",
      "zh": "今天早上，William 決定自己是一位勇敢的騎士，要保護我們的客廳不受一隻看不見的龍侵犯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "His sword was a wrapping paper tube. His shield was a garbage can lid. His battle plan was, honestly, nonexistent.",
      "zh": "他的劍是一根包裝紙的紙筒，他的盾牌是垃圾桶蓋，而他的作戰計畫，老實說，根本不存在。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He swung the tube at the invisible dragon, missed completely, and knocked over the lamp on the side table instead.",
      "zh": "他朝著那隻看不見的龍揮劍，完全揮空，反而把旁邊小桌上的檯燈給撞倒了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The lamp hit the floor with a terrible crash, and for one full second, the whole house went completely silent.",
      "zh": "檯燈砸到地上發出很可怕的巨響，接下來整整一秒，整間屋子安靜得可怕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Then William did something I will remember forever: he pointed at Perry and shouted, \"The dog did it!\"",
      "zh": "接著 William 做了一件我會永遠記得的事：他指著 Perry 大喊：「是狗做的！」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Perry, who was sleeping peacefully on the couch the entire time, opened one eye like he could not believe what he was hearing.",
      "zh": "Perry 這整段時間都在沙發上安穩地睡覺，聽到這句話只睜開一隻眼，一副不敢相信的表情。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Even a dog with a small brain knows when he is being framed for a crime he did not commit.",
      "zh": "就算是腦子不大的狗，也知道自己正被誣賴犯了一件牠沒做過的事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom came running in, took one look at the broken lamp, and asked the classic question every parent asks: \"What happened here?\"",
      "zh": "媽媽跑進來，看了一眼摔壞的檯燈，問出每個家長都會問的經典問題：「這裡發生什麼事了？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "William, still holding his cardboard sword, said, \"I have no idea. Maybe it fell by itself?\"",
      "zh": "William 手裡還握著他的紙板劍，說：「我不知道欸，說不定它自己就掉下來了？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "This excuse was so silly that even William himself did not sound like he believed it.",
      "zh": "這個藉口實在太蠢了，連 William 自己聽起來都不太相信。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom is not a foolish person; she raised two children and survived, which means she can spot a bad excuse from a mile away.",
      "zh": "媽媽不是個容易被騙的人；她養大了兩個小孩還活得好好的，代表她一眼就能看穿一個爛藉口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Lamps do not fall by themselves,\" Mom said calmly. \"And Perry cannot hold a sword. Try again.\"",
      "zh": "「檯燈不會自己掉下來，」媽媽平靜地說：「而且 Perry 也不會拿劍，再說一次。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "William's face turned a shade of red I did not know was possible, and he finally admitted the truth.",
      "zh": "William 的臉紅到我以前沒見過的程度，最後他終於承認了實話。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Fine, it was me,\" he said. \"But it was an accident! I was just being a knight!\"",
      "zh": "「好啦，是我，」他說：「但那是意外！我只是在當騎士而已！」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Being a knight, apparently, is a very dangerous hobby when your battlefield is our living room.",
      "zh": "顯然，如果你的戰場是我們家客廳，當騎士是一件相當危險的嗜好。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mom sat him down and explained that blaming an innocent dog would only make his punishment worse, not better.",
      "zh": "媽媽讓他坐下，解釋說把責任怪到一隻無辜的狗身上，只會讓他的懲罰更重，不會更輕。"
    },
    {
      "en": "William tried a different strategy: he looked at me with big, sad eyes, hoping I would take some of the blame too.",
      "zh": "William 換了一招：他用一雙可憐兮兮的大眼睛看著我，希望我也能幫他分擔一點責任。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"No,\" I said. \"I was upstairs the entire time. Nice try, though.\"",
      "zh": "「不要，」我說：「我整段時間都在樓上，不過你這招很不錯。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "His punishment, in the end, was fair: no video games for a week, and he had to clean up every piece of the broken lamp himself.",
      "zh": "最後他的懲罰算是公平：一個星期不能打電動，而且他要自己把摔破的檯燈碎片全部清乾淨。"
    },
    {
      "en": "He complained that a whole week felt like a heavy burden for one small accident, but Mom did not change her mind.",
      "zh": "他抱怨一個星期對一個小意外來說，感覺是很沉重的負擔，但媽媽並沒有因此改變心意。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia, watching from the kitchen doorway, shook her head and said something about how children today behave so differently from her own childhood.",
      "zh": "Sophia 從廚房門口看著這一切，搖搖頭說了幾句，現在的小孩行為舉止跟她小時候多麼不一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "I pointed out that Sophia has told us at least a dozen stories about her own childish tricks, including one about a stolen mango.",
      "zh": "我提醒她，Sophia 自己也講過至少十幾個她小時候調皮搗蛋的故事，其中一個還跟偷芒果有關。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Sophia laughed and admitted that was a fair point, and dropped the subject completely.",
      "zh": "Sophia 笑了出來，承認這一點說得有理，然後就不再提這件事了。"
    },
    {
